#!/usr/bin/env bash

cat <<-EOF

This is quick and dirty crontab(5) format help.

The time and date fields are:

    field           allowed values
    -----           --------------
    minute          0-59
    hour            0-23
    day of month    1-31
    month           1-12    (or names)
    day of week     0-7     (0 or 7 is Sunday, or names)

List:   "0,1,2,5,6,7" or "0-2,5-7"
Range:  "0-4", "*" (full range)
Step:   "0-23/2" or "*/2" - step of 2 (e.g., every two hours)

EOF
